<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-10121] Fix *NEW* failing pig unit tests</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10121</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The latest &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-6717&quot; title=&quot;Modernize schema tables&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-6717&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-6717&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; commit with the new driver deterministically broke the pig tests, and the issue is schema-related now.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/cassandra-3.0/job/cassandra-3.0_testall/lastCompletedBuild/testReport/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/cassandra-3.0/job/cassandra-3.0_testall/lastCompletedBuild/testReport/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ideally we want a fix before beta1.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12857026">CASSANDRA-10121</key>
            <summary>Fix *NEW* failing pig unit tests</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
